page.title: 10Railway Station, Manningtree
page.content: The railway links Manningtree to London and has operated on Diesel power for a long time and D class engines travelled here. Electric lines have been introduced on the route from Colchester to Ipswich. The Harwich and Ipswich to Norwich lines are in process of changing to electric power. The carriages and engines are old stock from the Western and the Midland region. It took 3 years to complete the electrification and 86 class engines have been suplied. The new engines were too light so concrete was put in the bottom. Recently the carriages have been refurnished inside and been given new livery outside. By Tony Jackson, 13 years old.
